-- News Corp.'s U.K. Newspaper COO Clive Milner Departs After Three Decades
-- B y   K r i s t e n   S c h w e i z e r
-- 2010-12-01T14:19:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-01/news-corp-u-k-newspaper-coo-clive-milner-departs-update1-.html
Clive Milner , chief operating officer
at  News Corp. ’s U.K. newspaper publishing unit, is leaving the
post after three decades, the company said in a statement today.  Milner helped to develop News International’s modern
printing plants and a more efficient distribution network for
the U.K. titles, which include the Times of London, the Sun and
News of the World, the statement said.  “Clive has been my colleague at News International for 30
years and in that time I have had great regard for the skill
with which he helped create the successful company we see
today,” News Corp. Chairman  Rupert Murdoch  said in the
statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Kristen Schweizer  in London at 
 kschweizer1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vidya Root at   vroot@bloomberg.net . 